16/10/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatian chief prosecutor Mladen Bajic and his Serbian counterpart, Vladimir Vukcevic, sealed a bilateral agreement Friday (October 13th) on co-operation in processing war crimes cases.
The document envisions the exchange of evidence and files related to conflicts in the former Yugoslavia.
According to a joint statement after the signing ceremony, the accord would enable the exchange of pertinent information, aimed at bringing all indictees to justice.
(Nezavisne novine - 14/10/06;
HINA - 13/10/06)
